,"sub_division":{"ikmk_subdivision_id":"11","subdivision_name_de":"Renaissance","subdivision_name_en":"Renaissance"},"literatur":"G. Habich, Die deutschen Schaum\u00fcnzen des XVI. Jahrhunderts I (1929) 95 Nr. 654 (dieses St\u00fcck erw\u00e4hnt).","comment":"Gegossene Bronzemedaille, oben gelocht. - Caspar Hedio (geb. 1494 zu Ettlingen, gest. 1552 in Stra\u00dfburg) war seit 1523 Domprediger in Stra\u00dfburg und heiratete hier 1524. Er f\u00fchrte in Stra\u00dfburg die Reformation ein. 1543 war er mit Melanchthon und Bucer in K\u00f6ln. Als Vorlage f\u00fcr das Portr\u00e4t diente m\u00f6glicherweise eine Silberstiftzeichnung von Hans Baldung Grien.","period":{"ikmk_period_id":"7","name_de":"Renaissance","name_en":"Renaissance","description_de":"Die Renaissance (Wiedergeburt) bezeichnet eine europ\u00e4ische Kunstperiode zwischen Mittelalter und Neuzeit im 15. und 16. Jahrhundert. Diese setzt im fr\u00fchen 15. Jahrhundert ein und wird um 1550 vom Barock abgel\u00f6st.","description_en":"The term Renaissance (rebirth) describes a period at the turn from the Middele Ages to the Modern period during the 15th and 16th century. It begins during the early 15th century and developes into the Baroque around 1550.","concept_id":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300021140","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/period\/7"},"year_start":"1543","year_end":"1543","date_verbal":"1543","year_islam":"0","references":[{"ikmk_referenz_id":221,"souce":"Habich, Schaum\u00fcnzen XVI. Jh.","number":"0654","similar":"0"}],"manufacturing":[{"ikmk_manufacturing_id":"22","manufacturing_name_de":"gegossen","manufacturing_name_en":"cast","nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/cast","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/manufacture\/22"}],"linked_persons_corporations":{"49":{"ikmk_type_id":"49","type_name_de":"Medailleur\/in","type_name_en":"Medalist","type_nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/medalist","type_concept_id":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4306105-9","ndp_id":"https:\/\/ikmk